            "id": "4465145",
            "title": "China's services growth at 9-month low to 50.6 in June",
            "description": "<html><body><p>The Caixin China General Services PMI declined to 50.6 in June 2025, down from May’s 51.1 and below market forecasts of 51.0, the weakest expansion in the services sector since September 2024, as growth in new orders eased and foreign sales recorded their sharpest decline since December 2022 amid subdued global conditions. </p>\n<p>The Caixin China General Composite PMI rose to 51.3 in June 2025 from 49.6 in the previous month, marking the highest reading since March. </p>\n<p>On Thursday, the <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SHCOMP?source=section%3Asearch_bar%7Ccontent_type%3Aall%7Csection_asset%3Asearch-basic%7Csearch_item%3Ashcomp%7Crow_num%3A1%7CURL_first_level%3Anews%7Ctopic%3Asymbol\">Shanghai Composite</a> rallied with the Shenzhen Component climbing 0.5% to above 10,460, following reports that the US has lifted certain export restrictions on chip design software to China, and the <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/USD:CNY#source=url_first_level%3Amarket-news%7Csection%3Aglobal%7Csection_asset%3Afull_story%7Cbutton%3Abody_link\">offshore yuan</a> steadied around 7.16 per dollar on Thursday as investors digested the latest PMI data.</p>\n<p>ETFs: (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FXI\">FXI</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KWEB\">KWEB</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CQQQ\">CQQQ</a>), (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MCHI\">MCHI</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ASHR\">ASHR</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/YINN\">YINN</a>), (NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TDF\">TDF</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CHIQ\">CHIQ</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GXC\">GXC</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EWH\">EWH</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KBA\">KBA</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/YANG\">YANG</a>), (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CXSE\">CXSE</a>), (NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CAF\">CAF</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CWEB\">CWEB</a>), (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PGJ\">PGJ</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KURE\">KURE</a>).</p>\n<p>Currency: (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CNY:USD\" title=\"Chinese Yuan / US Dollar\">CNY:USD</a>)</p>\n<h2>More on China markets and economy</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><p class=\"mb-0 text-share-text text-6x-large-r lg:text-4x-large-r\"><a class=\"font-bold text-inherit visited:text-inherit\" href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4465143-us-china-trade-agreement-leads-to-lifted-chip-design-software-restrictions#source=url_first_level%3Amarket-news%7Csection%3Amarket-pulse%7Csection_asset%3Anews_title\">U.S.-China trade agreement leads to lifted chip design software restrictions</a></p></li>\n<li><a class=\"font-bold text-inherit visited:text-inherit\" href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4456405-chinas-trade-surplus-widens-amid-weaker-exports-and-deeper-import-slump#source=url_first_level%3Amarket-news%7Csection%3Amarket-news%7Csection_asset%3Anews_title\">China's trade surplus widens amid weaker exports and deeper import slump</a></li>\n<li><p class=\"mb-0 text-share-text text-6x-large-r lg:text-4x-large-r\"><a class=\"font-bold text-inherit visited:text-inherit\" href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4456404-chinas-may-cpi-declines-fourth-consecutive-month-ppi-deflation-eases-to-two-year-low#source=url_first_level%3Amarket-news%7Csection%3Amarket-news%7Csection_asset%3Anews_title\">China’s May CPI declines fourth consecutive month, PPI deflation eases to two-year low</a></p></li>\n<li><a class=\"font-bold text-inherit visited:text-inherit\" href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4455400-chinas-services-sector-growth-accelerates-in-may-amid-stronger-business-activity#source=url_first_level%3Amarket-news%7Csection%3Amarket-news%7Csection_asset%3Anews_title\">China's services sector growth accelerates in May amid stronger business &amp; activity</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4454670-chinas-manufacturing-activity-unexpectedly-contracted-in-may-amid-weak-output-new-orders-and-exports\">China’s manufacturing activity unexpectedly contracted in May amid weak output, new orders, and exports</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p></body></html>",
