            "title": "Chinese AI start-up DeepSeek steps up hiring with job posts on LinkedIn",
            "description": "<html><body><div class=\"relative flex-col gap-1 md:gap-3\"><div class=\"flex max-w-full flex-col grow\"><div class=\"min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-5\" data-message-author-role=\"assistant\" data-message-id=\"cd29561b-a18e-4b43-9054-1d2c536c192b\" data-message-model-slug=\"gpt-4o\" dir=\"auto\"><div class=\"flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[3px]\"><div class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words light\"><ul>\n<li>DeepSeek (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DEEPSEEK\" title=\"Hangzhou DeepSeek Artificial Intelligence Co., Ltd.\">DEEPSEEK</a>) is stepping up its hiring efforts on LinkedIn, indicating the Chinese AI startup may be aiming to attract talent from beyond its home market.</li>\n<li>The Hangzhou-based company posted 10 positions on the Microsoft (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MSFT\" title=\"Microsoft Corporation\">MSFT</a>)-owned jobs and networking platform over the last week, its first listings for several months.</li>\n<li>The job listings, written in Mandarin, include three positions centered on artificial general intelligence, and are located in Beijing and Hangzhou.</li>\n<li>DeepSeek’s U.S. rivals, including OpenAI and Meta Platforms (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/META\" title=\"Meta Platforms, Inc.\">META</a>), have also been aggressively competing for <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4463513-meta-is-said-to-recruit-more-ai-talent-from-openai\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"top AI talent\">top AI talent</a> as they vie for leadership in a potentially transformative technology.</li>\n</ul></div></div></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"aria-live=polite absolute\">\n<div class=\"flex items-center justify-center\"> </div>\n<div class=\"flex items-center justify-center\"> </div>\n<div class=\"flex items-center justify-center\"> </div>\n</div>\n</body></html>",
